Name: trash-cli
Version: 0.11.3-r315
Summary: Command line interface to FreeDesktop.org Trash.
Home-page: http://code.google.com/p/trash-cli
Author: Andrea Francia
Author-email: andreafrancia@users.sourceforge.net
License: GPL v2
Download-URL: http://code.google.com/p/trash-cli/wiki/Download
Description: trash-cli - Command Line Interface to FreeDesktop.org Trash.
        
        trash-cli provides the following commands to manage the trash:
         * trash-put             trashes files and directories.
         * trash-empty           empty the trashcan(s).
         * trash-list            list trashed file.
         * trash-restore         restore a trashed file.
        
        For each file the name, original path, deletion date, and permissions
        are recorded. The trash command allow trash multiple files with the
        same name. These command uses the same Trashcan of last versions of
        KDE, GNOME and XFCE.
        
        Trash a file::
        
         $ trash-put /home/andrea/foobar
        
        List trashed files::
         
         $ trash-list
         2008-06-01 10:30:48 /home/andrea/bar
         2008-06-02 21:50:41 /home/andrea/bar
         2008-06-23 21:50:49 /home/andrea/foo
        
        Restore a trashed file::
        
         $ trash-restore /home/andrea/foo
        
        Empty the trashcan::
        
         $ trash-empty
        
Platform: UNKNOWN
